1
00:00:01,268 --> 00:00:04,269
[ Beeping ]                     


2
00:00:07,174 --> 00:00:09,741
    WHAT ARE WE DOING, SYDNEY?  


3
00:00:09,810 --> 00:00:12,811
AN EXPERIMENT                   
ABOUT SEXUALITY.                


4
00:00:12,879 --> 00:00:16,849
                REPRODUCTION?   
THAT'S ONE ASPECT OF IT.        


5
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:18,850
    I READ THE BIOLOGY MANUALS. 


6
00:00:18,919 --> 00:00:21,620
READING ISN'T QUITE             
THE SAME AS FEELING.            


7
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:24,789
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET            
SOMEONE, JAROD.                 


8
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:35,367
    <i> [ Beeping Increases ]</i>      


9
00:00:52,018 --> 00:00:55,387
YOU'RE A GIRL.                  
<i>[ Woman On TV ]</i>                 
<i>WILL YOU MARRY ME?</i>              


10
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:58,657
            NEVER. NO! OH!      
            <i> [ People Laughing ]</i>


11
00:00:58,726 --> 00:01:01,459
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>NOW WILL YOU MARRY ME?</i>          


12
00:01:01,528 --> 00:01:04,495
        THEY SEEM TO BE ABLE    
        TO WITHSTAND AN AMAZING 
        AMOUNT OF PAIN.         


13
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:10,402
        PEOPLE FIND THIS TYPE   
        OF VIOLENCE FUNNY?      


14
00:01:10,471 --> 00:01:13,438
    NOT PEOPLE, MEN.            
            <i> [ Men Laughing ]</i>   


15
00:01:13,507 --> 00:01:17,409
    -<i> [ Man On TV ] YOU MORON!</i>  
    - WHY IS THAT?              


16
00:01:17,478 --> 00:01:20,412
NOBODY KNOWS.                   
THE STOOGES HAVE BEEN ONE OF... 


17
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:22,781
THE GREAT MYSTERIES             
BETWEEN THE SEXES.              


18
00:01:22,850 --> 00:01:26,384
<i>[ Man On TV ] OW!</i>               
            [ Laughing ]        


19
00:01:26,453 --> 00:01:29,187
        I THINK I SEE IT.       
<i>[ Jarod Laughing ]</i>              


20
00:01:29,256 --> 00:01:32,524
    -<i> [ Man On TV ] MY PIANO!</i>   
    - OH, NOT YOU TOO.          


21
00:01:32,592 --> 00:01:37,496
        I'M SORRY, BUT, REALLY, 
        IT IS PRETTY FUNNY.     


22
00:01:37,564 --> 00:01:40,899
            [ Laughing ]        
            OH. OH.             


23
00:01:40,967 --> 00:01:43,435
I'M SORRY.                      
I FEEL LIKE SUCH A--            


24
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,504
                        STOOGE? 


25
00:01:47,174 --> 00:01:49,608
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>                


26
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:56,147
    <i> HEY, MATTRESS BRAIN,</i>       
    <i> THE BILL'S 12.95.</i>          


27
00:01:56,216 --> 00:01:58,149
                OH. OH.         


28
00:01:58,218 --> 00:02:00,419
THESE GUYS HAVE CAUSED          
ENOUGH DISTRACTIONS FOR ONE DAY.


29
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:03,655
<i>[ Men Laughing ]</i>                


30
00:02:03,724 --> 00:02:06,124
PARK SERVICE RANGERS            
FROM ALL OVER                   
HAVE JOINED IN THE SEARCH...    


31
00:02:06,193 --> 00:02:08,727
<i>FOR VICTOR SIMPKINS,</i>            
<i>AN ORNITHOLOGY GRAD STUDENT...</i>  


32
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:10,862
    WHO VANISHED                
    IN OUR LOCAL MOUNTAINS.     


33
00:02:10,931 --> 00:02:13,398
<i>I SPOKE WITH SIMPKINS'S MOTHER</i>  
<i>MOMENTS AGO.</i>                    


34
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:15,934
        <i> WHEN I DIDN'T HEAR</i>     
        <i> FROM VICTOR, WELL,</i>     


35
00:02:16,003 --> 00:02:19,804
    I JUST THOUGHT HE WAS LATE, 
    BUT NOW IT'S BEEN FIVE DAYS.


36
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:22,640
<i>I'M JUST PRAYING HE'S OKAY.</i>     


37
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:27,245
<i>WITH A STORM HEADING THIS WAY,</i>  
<i>RANGERS ARE ANXIOUS TO FIND</i>     
<i>SIMPKINS BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.</i>  


38
00:02:27,314 --> 00:02:31,182
LIVE FROM THE TOLUCA            
NATIONAL FOREST, THIS IS        
DAVID MILKSON,<i> ACTION 15.</i>       


39
00:02:31,251 --> 00:02:33,352
    OKAY, HERE'S YOUR--         
<i>[ Man #2 On TV ]</i>                
<i>THANK YOU, DAVID.</i>               


40
00:02:33,420 --> 00:02:35,153
<i>IN OTHER LOCAL NEWS--</i>           


41
00:02:35,222 --> 00:02:40,625
<i>I NEED ONE MORE BODY TO HELP</i>    
<i>SECTOR OUT SCOVELL RIDGE,</i>       
<i>B-1 THROUGH B-7.</i>                


42
00:02:40,694 --> 00:02:44,996
STEEP APPROACH, BAD UNDERBRUSH, 
A LOT OF SLIPPERY SHALE.        


43
00:02:45,065 --> 00:02:48,466
    - WHO WANTS TO HUMP THAT?   
    - I'M YOUR MAN.             


44
00:02:50,538 --> 00:02:54,039
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


45
00:03:37,617 --> 00:03:40,051
    - YOU GOT EXPERIENCE?       
    - I SPENT A FEW YEARS...    


46
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,320
        <i> IN THE ARMY RANGERS.</i>   


47
00:03:42,389 --> 00:03:45,624
- I SPECIALIZED IN              
  HIGH MOUNTAIN WORK.           
- MAN, YOU WERE MADE TO ORDER.  


48
00:03:45,692 --> 00:03:47,626
            <i> YOU COULD SAY THAT.</i>
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?               


49
00:03:47,694 --> 00:03:50,729
            JAROD... FOREST.    


50
00:03:50,797 --> 00:03:54,032
<i>ALL RIGHT, PEOPLE, LISTEN UP.</i>   
<i>ADVANCE PARTIES WENT UP AT DAWN.</i>


51
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:56,034
WE MOVE OUT IN 30 MINUTES.      


52
00:03:56,102 --> 00:04:00,471
<i>THIS KID'S BEEN MISSING</i>         
<i>FOR FIVE DAYS,</i>                  
<i>AND HIS MOTHER'S VERY CONCERNED.</i>


53
00:04:00,540 --> 00:04:04,442
HE-- WE ARE RUNNING             
OUT OF TIME,                    
SO WE LEAVE NO STONES UNTURNED. 


54
00:04:04,511 --> 00:04:08,780
WE'RE LOOKING FOR A NEEDLE,     
FOLKS, AND WE HAVEN'T EVEN      
FOUND THE HAYSTACK.             


55
00:04:10,384 --> 00:04:14,486
    -<i> FOREST. DEREK KOBEY.</i>      
    -<i> NICE TO MEET YOU.</i>         


56
00:04:14,555 --> 00:04:18,456
        SO, HAD ANYONE SEEN     
        VICTOR SIMPKINS BEFORE  
        HE WAS REPORTED MISSING?


57
00:04:18,525 --> 00:04:21,692
NO ONE WAS LOOKING FOR HIM.     
OF COURSE, FOR                  
THE LAST FEW DAYS,              


58
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:24,796
THE BOSS HAD ME                 
DOING PAPERWORK WHILE HE        
GOT TO DO ALL THE FUN STUFF.    


59
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:26,965
                FUN STUFF?      
<i>STAN'S BEEN ON THE NORTH SIDE...</i>


60
00:04:27,034 --> 00:04:29,000
OF THE MOUNTAIN CLEARING TRAILS,
SETTING CHARGES.                


61
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:32,070
<i>LOTS OF DEEP RAVINES,</i>           
<i>CAVES, FALLEN OLD GROWTH.</i>       


62
00:04:32,139 --> 00:04:36,307
<i>YOU TAKE A TUMBLE IN THAT, I</i>    
<i>DON'T CARE IF YOU'RE MOBY DICK,</i> 
<i>WE MIGHT NOT FIND YOU.</i>          


63
00:04:36,376 --> 00:04:38,877
        IT SOUNDS LIKE YOU KNOW 
        THE TERRAIN PRETTY WELL.


64
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,713
<i>EIGHT YEARS. I CAME OUT HERE</i>    
<i>ON ONE OF THOSE...</i>              


65
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:44,716
"LET'S EXPOSE THE URBAN YOUTH TO
 THE GREAT OUTDOORS" PROGRAMS.  


66
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,751
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>HEY, DEREK.</i>                     
    FUNNY THING IS, IT WORKED.  


67
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:50,521
<i>PHONE.</i>                          
        I LOVE THE BRONX,       
        BUT THIS IS HOME NOW.   


68
00:04:56,096 --> 00:05:00,699
SO, FOREST,                     
WHERE DID YOU DO YOUR           
MOUNTAIN TRAINING?              


69
00:05:00,768 --> 00:05:04,001
    - IN THE MOUNTAINS, MOSTLY. 
    - YEAH.                     


70
00:05:04,071 --> 00:05:07,305
NO, SERIOUSLY, WHERE WERE       
YOU STATIONED? FORT LEWIS?      


71
00:05:07,374 --> 00:05:09,875
    YOU WERE IN THE ARMY TOO?   
<i>FIFTEEN YEARS.</i>                  


72
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:13,945
<i>YOU EVER COME ACROSS</i>            
<i>A SERGEANT TRIPCHECK,</i>           
<i>A RANGER INSTRUCTOR AT BENNING?</i> 


73
00:05:14,013 --> 00:05:17,615
    - SOUNDS FAMILIAR.          
    - HE'S LYING, STAN.         


74
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,853
HE'S REALLY ONE OF THE STOOGES. 


75
00:05:21,922 --> 00:05:25,523
- YOU TWO KNOW EACH OTHER?      
- WE RAN INTO EACH OTHER ONCE.  


76
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:33,531
    - IS SHE A RANGER?          
    - NO. SHE'S A VOLUNTEER.    


77
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:37,368
<i>SHE RUNS A LITTLE OUTFITTING</i>    
<i>PLACE A FEW MILES DOWN THE ROAD.</i>


78
00:05:37,437 --> 00:05:41,172
I WOULDN'T GET ANY IDEAS.       
SHE KEEPS MOSTLY TO HERSELF.    


79
00:05:41,241 --> 00:05:43,742
<i>STAN, JUST GOT WORD</i>             
<i>FROM THE ADVANCE TEAM.</i>          


80
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:47,145
    - THEY FOUND SIMPKINS'S     
      BASE CAMP.                
    -<i> [ Radio Chatter ]</i>         


81
00:05:50,117 --> 00:05:53,285
WE'LL SPLIT INTO TEAMS OF TWO   
AND FAN ACROSS THE MOUNTAIN.    


82
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:55,954
I WANT EVERYONE TO REPORT IN    
AT 30-MINUTE INTERVALS.         


83
00:05:56,023 --> 00:05:58,256
<i>[ Man On Radio ]</i>                
<i>STANDING BY FOR AN UPDATE.</i>      
<i>I NEED FLARES OVER HERE.</i>        


84
00:05:58,325 --> 00:06:00,325
WHERE'S FOREST?                 


85
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:06,264
    DISTURBANCE IN THE FORCE?   


86
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:08,833
        - UH, THE FORCE?        
        - OBI-WAN KENOBI?       


87
00:06:08,901 --> 00:06:11,102
                    STAR WARS?  


88
00:06:11,170 --> 00:06:16,074
    - THE SATELLITE MISSILE     
      DEFENSE SYSTEM?           
    - WHAT ARE YOU DOING?       


89
00:06:16,143 --> 00:06:20,778
I'M JUST TRYING TO IMAGINE      
WHAT KIND OF PERSON VICTOR IS...


90
00:06:20,848 --> 00:06:25,917
<i>AND WHO WOULD WANT TO SPEND</i>     
<i>MONTHS IN ISOLATION ON PURPOSE.</i> 


91
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:28,019
        SOMEBODY WHO'S TRYING   
        TO FIND HIMSELF?        


92
00:06:28,087 --> 00:06:29,955
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE WILDERNESS?


93
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:33,825
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO GET LOST  
BEFORE YOU CAN FIND YOURSELF.   


94
00:06:36,597 --> 00:06:39,397
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>ONE MORE MAN FOR THE TEAM.</i>      


95
00:06:40,567 --> 00:06:42,967
        MRS. SIMPKINS?          
        HI, I'M JAROD FOREST.   


96
00:06:43,036 --> 00:06:46,470
I WAS WONDERING IF I MIGHT      
ASK YOU SOME QUESTIONS          
ABOUT YOUR SON.                 


97
00:06:46,539 --> 00:06:48,606
    ANYTHING TO HELP.           


98
00:06:48,675 --> 00:06:52,610
    - IS VICTOR RIGHT-HANDED    
      OR LEFT-HANDED?           
    - HE'S RIGHT-HANDED.        


99
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:57,915
I NOTICED THAT HE HAD           
MANY BOOKS ON PREDATORY BIRDS.  


100
00:06:57,985 --> 00:07:01,285
HE'S BEEN OUT HERE FOR MONTHS   
DOCUMENTING THE NESTING PATTERNS
OF EAGLES.                      


101
00:07:01,354 --> 00:07:03,955
<i>HE'S LOVED THEM SINCE</i>           
<i>HE WAS A LITTLE BOY.</i>            


102
00:07:04,024 --> 00:07:07,926
HE USED TO SIT OUT IN FRONT OF  
HIS TENT AND WATCH THEM ALL DAY.


103
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:11,395
HE'S THE ONLY FAMILY I HAVE.    


104
00:07:11,464 --> 00:07:14,299
                DON'T WORRY.    
                WE'LL FIND HIM. 


105
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:18,737
- WE WON'T LEAVE THE MOUNTAIN   
  UNTIL WE DO.                  
- THIS WAY, MRS. SIMPKINS.      


106
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:26,644
- SO WHO AM I PAIRED WITH, STAN?
- MOE.                          


107
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:33,151
            YOU LOOK CONFUSED.  
        I AM CONFUSED.          


108
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:35,153
    VICTOR HAD BEEN OUT HERE    
    FOR MONTHS,                 


109
00:07:35,222 --> 00:07:37,889
    YET THERE WAS NO SIGN OF    
    A REFUSE PILE OR A LATRINE? 


110
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:40,292
                        MEANING?
    I DON'T KNOW.               


111
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:44,729
    JUST ANOTHER PIECE          
    OF THE PUZZLE.              
YOU'RE A STRANGE STOOGE, MOE.   


112
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:47,432
    WHAT ABOUT THAT LEFT-HAND,  
    RIGHT-HAND STUFF?           


113
00:07:47,501 --> 00:07:50,368
<i>VICTOR'S EYEGLASSES WERE ON</i>     
<i>THE LEFT-HAND SIDE OF</i>           
<i>HIS SLEEPING BAG.</i>               


114
00:07:50,436 --> 00:07:53,038
SEEMS KIND OF AWKWARD           
FOR A RIGHT-HANDED MAN.         


115
00:07:53,106 --> 00:07:57,309
        THIS WAY. JAROD?        


116
00:07:57,377 --> 00:07:59,977
SOMEBODY'S COVERED THEIR TRACKS 
BY BRUSHING OVER THEM.          


117
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,350
        <i> THEY HEAD UP THAT WAY.</i> 


118
00:08:44,825 --> 00:08:46,157
                    AAH! AAH!   


119
00:08:48,395 --> 00:08:52,563
- I DIDN'T MEAN TO STARTLE YOU. 
- THAT'S OKAY. I'LL LIVE.       


120
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:54,566
    ABOUT TWO WEEKS LESS,       
    BUT I'LL LIVE.              


121
00:08:54,634 --> 00:08:56,133
                HI.             


122
00:08:56,203 --> 00:08:58,403
I'M JAROD, AND THIS IS NIA.     


123
00:08:58,472 --> 00:09:01,405
        <i> BOB. SORRY, JAROD.</i>     
        <i> YOU STARTLED ME.</i>       


124
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,908
CAN'T SHAKE THE HAND            
OF A MAN WHO JUST STARTLED ME.  


125
00:09:03,977 --> 00:09:05,910
        I HAVE TO WAIT TILL     
        THE NEXT TIME I SEE YOU.


126
00:09:05,979 --> 00:09:09,680
    - ARE YOU HIDING            
      FROM SOMEONE, BOB?        
    - HIDING? I'M LOOKING.      


127
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:12,016
    OH. OH, YOU'RE WITH         
    THE SEARCH PARTY.           


128
00:09:12,085 --> 00:09:14,251
    SEARCH PARTY? THEY GOT      
    A SEARCH PARTY TO FIND BOB? 


129
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:17,688
    -<i> I THOUGHT YOU WERE BOB.</i>   
    - I AM BOB, BIG BOB.        


130
00:09:17,758 --> 00:09:20,258
        LOOKING FOR LITTLE BOB. 
        HE'S MY PARTNER.        


131
00:09:20,326 --> 00:09:22,393
    OH, UH--                    


132
00:09:22,462 --> 00:09:25,797
<i>WE'RE LOOKING FOR A STUDENT.</i>    
        HIS CAMP WAS ABOUT      
        THREE MILES WEST.       


133
00:09:25,865 --> 00:09:29,600
<i>BROWN HAIR, ABOUT 5'11".</i>        
                DON'T KNOW HIM. 


134
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:32,604
        DON'T KNOW HIS CAMP.    
        I AIN'T SEEN NOTHING.   


135
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:35,406
<i>SHOULD WE ALERT SOMEONE</i>         
<i>ABOUT LITTLE BOB?</i>               


136
00:09:35,475 --> 00:09:37,842
        NO, YOU DON'T WANT      
        TO GET MY PARTNER MAD.  


137
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:41,446
    I'VE SEEN HIM GO INTO A BAR 
    AND TEAR IT UP FROM         
    ONE END TO THE OTHER.       


138
00:09:41,514 --> 00:09:44,081
HOW WILL WE KNOW HIM            
IF WE FIND HIM?                 
    <i> YOU DON'T WANT TO FIND HIM.</i>


139
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:47,786
        HE DON'T LIKE STRANGERS.
        TRUTH BE TOLD,          
        HE DON'T LIKE ANYBODY.  


140
00:09:47,854 --> 00:09:50,287
                [ Sniffing ]    


141
00:09:53,393 --> 00:09:56,527
            BAD STORM COMING.   
             BAD ONE.           


142
00:09:59,132 --> 00:10:02,133
    - [ Chuckles ]              
    -<i> [ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>      


143
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:06,170
<i>AND BEFORE THE RANGERS?</i>         


144
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:11,308
TEST PILOT, THORACIC SURGEON,   
LIEUTENANT COMMANDER            
ON A DESTROYER.                 


145
00:10:11,377 --> 00:10:15,145
THE USUAL. WHAT DID YOU DO      
BEFORE YOU BECAME AN OUTFITTER? 


146
00:10:15,214 --> 00:10:19,250
ASTRONAUT, OLYMPIC SKATER,      
NOBEL PRIZE WINNER.             


147
00:10:19,318 --> 00:10:21,318
    THE USUAL.                  


148
00:10:23,657 --> 00:10:25,322
        [ Nia ]                 
        WHAT'S THAT OVER THERE? 


149
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:31,929
        <i> IT'S A CARABINEER.</i>     
        <i> I'M GOING TO GET IT.</i>   


150
00:10:31,998 --> 00:10:34,632
NO CLIMBER WOULD                
LEAVE THAT BEHIND.              


151
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:38,836
BE CAREFUL.                     
YOU DON'T KNOW THESE CLIFFS.    
IT'S DANGEROUS.                 


152
00:10:38,905 --> 00:10:42,807
        RELAX. I WAS A SHERPA   
        ON MOUNT EVEREST ONCE.  


153
00:10:44,277 --> 00:10:45,843
            REALLY.             


154
00:10:54,721 --> 00:10:57,288
                BE CAREFUL.     


155
00:11:05,132 --> 00:11:07,198
    THESE MARKINGS ARE FRESH.   


156
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:09,400
        LOOKS LIKE IT'S ONLY    
        A FEW DAYS OLD.         


157
00:11:12,371 --> 00:11:14,138
JAROD!                          


158
00:11:16,476 --> 00:11:17,842
            [ Shouts ]          


159
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:24,048
COME ON.                        


160
00:11:26,552 --> 00:11:28,152
    OW!                         


161
00:11:36,262 --> 00:11:40,231
        <i> THAT'S VICTOR'S MARK.</i>  
        <i> ORANGE TAPE.</i>           


162
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:42,233
    THE INUIT SIGN FOR EAGLE.   


163
00:11:42,302 --> 00:11:44,902
    HE SAID ANYBODY             
    COULD USE THEIR INITIALS.   


164
00:11:46,606 --> 00:11:48,606
    HE'S AN EXPERIENCED CLIMBER.


165
00:11:48,675 --> 00:11:52,076
HE WOULDN'T LEAVE HIS EQUIPMENT 
BEHIND UNLESS--                 


166
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:57,314
LISTEN, THE SUN RISES AT 6:35.  


167
00:11:57,383 --> 00:12:01,019
WE DEPLOY HERE FROM K-4 TO K-8, 
JUST BELOW THE CLIFF.           


168
00:12:01,087 --> 00:12:03,320
I WANT EVERYONE HERE            
AT QUARTER OF 6:00.             


169
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:05,690
THERE'S A COLD FRONT MOVING     
THROUGH IN THE NEXT 48 HOURS.   


170
00:12:05,758 --> 00:12:07,892
            WILL MY SON         
            BE ABLE TO SURVIVE? 


171
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:10,761
        YOUR SON IS             
        AN EXPERIENCED CLIMBER. 


172
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:14,565
<i>HE MAY BE COLD,</i>                 
<i>AND HE MAY BE HUNGRY,</i>           
<i>BUT PEOPLE HAVE SURVIVED WORSE.</i> 


173
00:12:14,634 --> 00:12:18,235
I KNOW HE'S OUT THERE SOMEWHERE,
WORRYING ABOUT YOU TOO.         


174
00:12:19,639 --> 00:12:22,139
EVERYBODY, GET SOME SLEEP.      


175
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:24,408
WE HEAD OUT AT                  
THE CRACK OF DAWN.              


176
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:29,146
HEY, KOBEY,                     
WHERE'S THE NEAREST MOTEL?      
                ABOUT 100 MILES.


177
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:31,415
AND WHEN YOU GET THERE,         
YOU'LL WISH IT WAS ANOTHER 100. 


178
00:12:31,485 --> 00:12:34,252
<i>I'VE GOT A SPARE ROOM.</i>          
<i>GRAB YOUR GEAR.</i>                 


179
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,487
<i>I'LL WAIT FOR YOU OUTSIDE.</i>      


180
00:12:40,193 --> 00:12:42,127
    MAN, THAT MUST'VE BEEN      
    SOME SEARCH UP THERE TODAY. 


181
00:12:42,195 --> 00:12:44,228
                HMM?            


182
00:12:44,296 --> 00:12:48,099
    SENORITA ICEBERG INVITES YOU
    OVER FOR A SLUMBER PARTY?   


183
00:12:48,168 --> 00:12:52,804
YOU ARE IN.                     
                IN WHERE?       


184
00:12:57,077 --> 00:13:00,411
COUCH IS OLD, AND EXCEPT FOR    
A SPRING OR TWO IN YOUR BACK,   


185
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,947
IT'S COMFORTABLE.               


186
00:13:03,016 --> 00:13:05,316
    I'M SURE IT WILL BE FINE.   


187
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:12,924
        THE<i> CASA ROSADA.</i>        
        YOU'RE ARGENTINEAN.     


188
00:13:12,993 --> 00:13:14,925
            <i> IS THIS YOU</i>        
            <i> WITH YOUR PARENTS?</i> 


189
00:13:14,995 --> 00:13:17,862
NOT TOO MANY GRINGOS KNOW ABOUT 
THE ARGENTINEAN WHITE HOUSE.    


190
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,930
I'M IMPRESSED.                  


191
00:13:21,368 --> 00:13:24,002
<i>IS THAT EVERYTHING?</i>             
        I TRAVEL LIGHT.         


192
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:28,339
        - ON THE RUN?           
        - SOME DAYS.            


193
00:13:31,845 --> 00:13:35,246
I DO A LOT OF CONSULTING WORK.  


194
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:41,886
    TAKE OFF YOUR SHIRT.        


195
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:47,325
            WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY  
            IT WAS SO BAD?      


196
00:13:47,394 --> 00:13:49,727
I GUESS I DIDN'T REALIZE IT.    


197
00:14:13,753 --> 00:14:16,153
        I'LL TRY TO LEAVE SOME  
        HOT WATER FOR YOU.      


198
00:14:16,222 --> 00:14:18,056
                        <i> OKAY?</i>  


199
00:14:43,016 --> 00:14:44,281
[ Beeping ]                     


200
00:14:44,350 --> 00:14:46,351
        YOU'RE A GIRL.          


201
00:14:53,259 --> 00:14:57,095
        MY NAME IS JAROD.       
        WHAT'S YOUR NAME?       


202
00:15:05,372 --> 00:15:07,772
            MISS PARKER.        


203
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:23,488
        SHOWER'S ALL YOURS.     


204
00:15:27,059 --> 00:15:28,993
            SLEEP WELL.         


205
00:15:29,062 --> 00:15:31,162
        YOU TOO.                


206
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:44,008
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


207
00:15:44,076 --> 00:15:47,544
    -<i> THIS IS SYDNEY.</i>           
    - [ Jarod ] IT'S ME.        


208
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:51,983
        I NEED TO TALK TO YOU...
        ABOUT WOMEN.            


209
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:56,621
    - WHY IS THAT?              
    - BECAUSE I MET ONE.        


210
00:16:02,762 --> 00:16:07,331
<i>[ Nia ] NO!</i>                     
<i>[ Shouting In Spanish ]</i>         


211
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:11,335
        [ Spanish ]             


212
00:16:11,403 --> 00:16:13,404
<i>[ Shouting Continues ]</i>          


213
00:16:15,574 --> 00:16:17,408
        <i> IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.</i>  
         <i> IT'S ALL RIGHT.</i>       


214
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:20,511
        IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.   
        YOU'RE SAFE.            


215
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:27,318
                    [ Jarod ]   
                    IT'S ME.    


216
00:16:27,386 --> 00:16:30,721
        I NEED TO TALK TO YOU...
        ABOUT WOMEN.            


217
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:33,057
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>WHY IS THAT?</i>                    


218
00:16:33,126 --> 00:16:36,560
            <i> BECAUSE I MET ONE.</i> 
<i>TELL ME MORE.</i>                   


219
00:16:36,629 --> 00:16:38,996
    <i> I'VE BEEN AROUND HUNDREDS</i>  
    <i> OF WOMEN SINCE I LEFT,</i>     


220
00:16:39,065 --> 00:16:42,834
    <i> BUT I NEVER EXPERIENCED</i>    
    <i> WITH THEM WHAT I FEEL</i>      
    <i> WITH THE ONE I'VE JUST MET.</i>


221
00:16:42,902 --> 00:16:46,370
<i>TELL ME ABOUT YOUR FEELINGS.</i>    
    <i> I HAVE A HARD TIME FOCUSING</i>
    <i> WHEN I'M NEAR HER.</i>         


222
00:16:46,439 --> 00:16:50,074
    <i> AND IF WE HAPPEN TO TOUCH,</i> 
    <i> MY HEART RATE,</i>             


223
00:16:50,143 --> 00:16:52,543
            <i> MY BLOOD PRESSURE,</i> 
            <i> EVEN MY BREATHING</i>  
            <i> BECOMES ERRATIC.</i>   


224
00:16:52,612 --> 00:16:54,578
FRANKENBOY HAS A GIRLFRIEND.    


225
00:16:54,647 --> 00:16:57,914
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>IT'S CHEMICAL, JAROD.</i>           
                    <i> CHEMICAL?</i>  


226
00:16:57,983 --> 00:16:59,884
<i>THE FEELINGS YOU'RE HAVING--</i>    


227
00:16:59,953 --> 00:17:04,555
<i>THEY'RE DRIVEN BY</i>               
<i>YOUR BODY'S RESPONSE</i>            
<i>TO AN EXTERNAL STIMULUS.</i>        


228
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:08,593
<i>IN THIS CASE, A WOMAN.</i>          
        <i> TONIGHT, WHEN SHE CAME</i> 
        <i> OUT OF THE SHOWER--</i>    


229
00:17:08,661 --> 00:17:11,595
                    <i> [ Broots ]</i> 
                    <i> THERE.</i>     
    WHAT ARE YOU DOING?         


230
00:17:11,664 --> 00:17:16,167
THAT'S WHERE THE RADIO          
IN THE BACKGROUND IS CLEAREST.  


231
00:17:16,235 --> 00:17:20,304
A LITTLE PRESTO-CHANGO,         
AND MAYBE WE CAN FILTER IT OUT  
AND FIGURE OUT THE SONG.        


232
00:17:20,373 --> 00:17:22,273
I DIDN'T HEAR ANY RADIO.        


233
00:17:22,342 --> 00:17:24,275
I WOULD LIKE TO HEAR            
THE REST OF THE TAPE.           


234
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:27,978
MAYBE THERE'S A CLUE            
YOU MIGHT HAVE MISSED.          


235
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,649
            [ Clears Throat ]   


236
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:34,652
        <i> [ Stan ]</i>               
        <i> NOW IF VICTOR SIMPKINS</i> 
        <i> WENT DOWN HERE,</i>        


237
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:38,289
<i>HE HAD TO GO THROUGH AN AREA</i>    
<i>BETWEEN THIS CLIFF FACE</i>         
<i>AND THE RIVER.</i>                  


238
00:17:38,358 --> 00:17:41,792
        ANYBODY FIND ANYTHING,  
        WE'RE ON CHANNEL NINE.  


239
00:17:41,861 --> 00:17:43,961
        ALL RIGHT.              
        LET'S MOVE OUT, QUICKLY.


240
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:53,971
WE FOUND SIMPKINS'S             
CARABINEER HERE, RIGHT?         


241
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:57,141
                YES. WHY?       


242
00:17:57,209 --> 00:17:59,977
    THE FORCE STILL WITH YOU?   


243
00:18:00,046 --> 00:18:03,580
WHY CROSS A CLIFF THAT DANGEROUS
WHEN YOU CAN HIKE AROUND IT?    


244
00:18:03,649 --> 00:18:09,453
MAYBE HE JUST GOT THE URGE.     
PEOPLE DON'T ALWAYS PLAN THINGS.


245
00:18:09,522 --> 00:18:12,957
NO, I GUESS THEY DON'T.         


246
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:20,798
        THANKS FOR              
        BEING THERE LAST NIGHT. 


247
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:24,768
WHAT DID YOU MEAN WHEN YOU SAID,
"I DON'T WANT TO DISAPPEAR"?    


248
00:18:24,837 --> 00:18:26,937
                I SAID THAT?    
<i>TWICE.</i>                          


249
00:18:27,006 --> 00:18:30,508
- IN SPANISH.                   
- YOU MUST'VE MISUNDERSTOOD ME. 


250
00:18:30,577 --> 00:18:33,277
<i>HABLO ESPANOL MUY BIEN.</i>         


251
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:41,785
    <i> [ Clears Throat ]</i>          
    <i> I SAID, "HERE'S</i>            
    <i> THE TAPE COPY YOU WANTED."</i> 


252
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:45,889
        OF JAROD'S CONVERSATION.


253
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:48,526
ARE YOU STILL HERE?             


254
00:18:48,595 --> 00:18:50,595
                        UH, NO. 


255
00:19:03,843 --> 00:19:06,743
<i>[ Young Miss Parker ]</i>           
<i>YOU'RE AFRAID OF ME, AREN'T YOU?</i>


256
00:19:08,614 --> 00:19:12,249
    - NO.                       
    - YOU WERE YESTERDAY.       


257
00:19:12,318 --> 00:19:15,987
        - I COULD TELL.         
        - I WAS NERVOUS.        


258
00:19:17,389 --> 00:19:21,024
    - YOU HAVE SOFT SKIN.       
    - YOU DIDN'T EVEN TOUCH ME. 


259
00:19:21,094 --> 00:19:23,694
            YES, I DID. IN HERE.


260
00:19:25,098 --> 00:19:28,099
            HOLD OUT YOUR HAND  
            LIKE THIS.          


261
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:36,006
                CAN YOU FEEL IT?


262
00:19:43,816 --> 00:19:47,384
            WHAT'S YOUR NAME?   
            YOUR<i> FIRST</i> NAME?    


263
00:19:56,295 --> 00:19:58,295
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]     


264
00:20:07,307 --> 00:20:09,973
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>SO LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.</i>    


265
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:14,378
<i>THEY WERE CALLED</i>                
<i>"THE THREE STOOGES,"</i>            
<i>BUT THERE WERE ACTUALLY FOUR.</i>   


266
00:20:14,447 --> 00:20:18,682
            WITH SHEMP.         
            FIVE IF YOU COUNT   
            JOE BESSER.         


267
00:20:18,751 --> 00:20:20,952
                THOUGH A LOT    
                OF PEOPLE DON'T.


268
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:25,022
AND SIX IF YOU INCLUDE          
CURLY-JOE DeRITA.               


269
00:20:25,091 --> 00:20:27,291
BUT HE WASN'T EVEN              
FUNNY IN SPANISH.               
[ Laughs ]                      


270
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:29,025
            [ Jarod Laughs ]    


271
00:20:29,094 --> 00:20:31,127
WAS LARRY ONE                   
OF THE BROTHERS?                
                        NO.     


272
00:20:31,196 --> 00:20:33,263
MOE, CURLY AND--                
<i>[ Twig Snaps ]</i>                  


273
00:20:33,332 --> 00:20:35,265
WHAT?                           
    I THOUGHT I HEARD SOMETHING.


274
00:20:35,334 --> 00:20:36,967
            <i> [ Shouting ]</i>       


275
00:20:40,206 --> 00:20:42,339
        ARE YOU OKAY?           
                    [ Groaning ]


276
00:20:43,776 --> 00:20:46,076
    SORRY. I CAN'T              
    SHAKE YOUR HAND JUST YET.   


277
00:20:47,212 --> 00:20:49,279
    THIS IS THE SECOND TIME     
    YOU'VE SEEN ME.             


278
00:20:49,348 --> 00:20:53,417
    EXCEPT YOU JUST WALKED      
    BETWEEN TWO PINE TREES.     
    AIN'T NEVER GONNA HAPPEN.   


279
00:20:55,121 --> 00:20:57,655
DID YOU FIND YOUR PARTNER?      
                    NO.         


280
00:20:57,724 --> 00:21:00,424
        I GOTTA KEEP CHECKING   
        ON MY CROP,             
        EVEN WITHOUT HIM.       


281
00:21:00,493 --> 00:21:02,559
CHECKING ON YOUR CROP?          
                        <i> YEAH.</i>  


282
00:21:02,628 --> 00:21:06,630
    - NOW I GOTTA DO            
      LITTLE BOB'S JOB TOO.     
    - IS HE SICK?               


283
00:21:06,699 --> 00:21:10,467
        NERVES. HAD THE SHAKES  
        EVER SINCE THAT PLANE   
        BUZZED HIM LAST FRIDAY. 


284
00:21:10,536 --> 00:21:12,836
        <i> AND THEN THE DYNAMITE.</i> 
        <i> [ Laughs ]</i>             


285
00:21:12,905 --> 00:21:14,939
        THAT JUST ABOUT         
        PUT HIM OVER THE TOP.   


286
00:21:15,007 --> 00:21:17,441
SOMEONE WAS SETTING OFF         
DYNAMITE OUT HERE?              


287
00:21:17,510 --> 00:21:22,145
YEAH, RANGER CONRAD WAS CLEARING
THE TRAIL OF SOME OLD STUMPS.   


288
00:21:22,214 --> 00:21:25,382
-<i> [ Man ] SECTOR 4, COME IN.</i>    
- FOREST HERE.                  


289
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:28,652
I FOUND VICTOR SIMPKINS'S       
PACK ABOUT A QUARTER            
OF A MILE DOWNSTREAM...         


290
00:21:28,721 --> 00:21:32,256
    FROM THE CLIFF,             
    LODGED IN SOME DEBRIS       
    ALONG THE RIVERBANK.        


291
00:21:32,325 --> 00:21:34,325
        SIMPKINS'S TRACKS       
        LED RIGHT TO THE WATER. 


292
00:21:34,393 --> 00:21:36,527
    <i> I'M GUESSING HE GOT HURT</i>   
    <i> IN THE FALL FROM THE CLIFF,</i>


293
00:21:36,596 --> 00:21:39,729
        <i> MADE IT TO THE WATER,</i>  
        <i> PASSED OUT</i>             
        <i> OR SLIPPED AND FELL IN.</i>


294
00:21:39,798 --> 00:21:44,201
IF HE DIDN'T DROWN,             
HE'S SOMEWHERE DOWNRIVER...     


295
00:21:44,270 --> 00:21:47,138
OR IN THE PACIFIC.              
            <i> [ Mrs. Simpkins ]</i>  
            <i> OH, MY GOD!</i>        


296
00:21:47,206 --> 00:21:51,708
ARE YOU CALLING OFF             
THE SEARCH FOR MY SON?          
                    NO, MA'AM.  


297
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:54,845
    I'M SHIFTING PERSONNEL      
    AND OVERSIGHT TO THE ANAWALT
    COUNTY SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT,


298
00:21:54,913 --> 00:21:57,548
    WHO'S GOT DIRECT SUPERVISION
    OF THE RIVER                
    FROM HERE TO THE COAST.     


299
00:21:57,617 --> 00:22:00,651
        NOW, LISTEN,            
        I CALLED SHERIFF HANSEN.


300
00:22:00,719 --> 00:22:04,154
        HE'S A GOOD MAN.        
        HE'LL DO WHATEVER HE CAN
        TO HELP FIND VICTOR.    


301
00:22:04,223 --> 00:22:06,923
COME WITH ME, MRS. SIMPKINS.    


302
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:27,578
HE'S GOT ENOUGH GEAR AND FOOD   
TO CLIMB FOR DAYS.              


303
00:22:27,646 --> 00:22:30,714
            HE WAS DOCUMENTING  
            THE NESTING PATTERNS
            OF EAGLES.          


304
00:22:34,153 --> 00:22:36,720
THERE'S NOTHING HERE            
TO WRITE ON.                    


305
00:22:36,788 --> 00:22:38,722
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.          


306
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:43,059
HIS CAMP, HIS CARABINEER,       
THIS-- THIS BACKPACK.           


307
00:22:43,128 --> 00:22:45,762
        <i> [ Nia ]</i>                
        <i> BUT WHAT DOES IT MEAN?</i> 


308
00:22:45,831 --> 00:22:49,133
SOMEONE WANTS THE SEARCH        
FOR VICTOR TO GO DOWNSTREAM.    


309
00:22:50,536 --> 00:22:52,502
            YOU'RE NOT GOING,   
            ARE YOU?            


310
00:22:52,571 --> 00:22:55,405
NO.                             


311
00:22:55,474 --> 00:22:57,407
HE'S STILL ON THIS MOUNTAIN.    


312
00:23:05,284 --> 00:23:07,951
            CAN ANYBODY HEAR ME?


313
00:23:08,020 --> 00:23:10,420
                [ Coughing ]    


314
00:23:12,625 --> 00:23:15,626
            <i> [ Shower Running ]</i> 


315
00:23:28,241 --> 00:23:31,108
[ Young Sydney ]                
JAROD,<i> APOLLO 1</i> SIMULATION.     


316
00:23:31,177 --> 00:23:35,813
THE FIRST WARNING IS A FLASH    
AS THE SPARK IGNITES            
THE PURE OXYGEN IN THE CAPSULE. 


317
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:41,585
I TRY TO FLEE, BUT I CAN'T.     
I'M STRAPPED IN.                


318
00:23:41,654 --> 00:23:45,689
I KNOW THE ESCAPE PROCEDURE,    
BUT THE FIRE, IT'S TOO HOT.     


319
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:50,527
IT COMES INTO MY AIR LINES.     
I TRY NOT TO BREATHE,           
BUT IT'S TOO LATE.<i> </i>             


320
00:23:50,596 --> 00:23:53,931
I CAN'T OPEN THE HATCH.         
 I CAN'T OPEN THE HATCH!        


321
00:23:53,999 --> 00:23:56,132
IT'S TOO HOT!                   
I CAN'T THINK!                  


322
00:23:56,201 --> 00:23:59,103
NO ONE CAN GET TO US!           
WE CAN'T BE SAVED!              


323
00:23:59,172 --> 00:24:02,105
I'M BURNING! I'M BURNING!       


324
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:06,143
JAROD! I'M HERE. IT'S ALL RIGHT.


325
00:24:06,212 --> 00:24:08,212
    NO ONE COULD SAVE THEM.     


326
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:11,681
    IT WAS IMPOSSIBLE.          


327
00:24:15,321 --> 00:24:17,821
            <i> I TRIED NOT TO USE</i> 
            <i> ALL THE HOT WATER.</i> 


328
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:26,297
<i>[ Closes Briefcase ]</i>            


329
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:33,970
                IS THAT BOY YOU?


330
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:39,476
    - I KNOW IT'S CRAZY,        
      BUT I CAN EXPLAIN.        
    - SHH.                      


331
00:24:43,516 --> 00:24:45,816
            WE ALL HAVE SCARS.  


332
00:24:52,058 --> 00:24:55,158
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>HOW MUCH LONGER, BROOTS?</i>        
<i>HARD TO SAY.</i>                    


333
00:24:55,227 --> 00:24:57,794
AT FIRST, I THOUGHT THE SONG    
FROM JAROD'S PHONE CALL...      


334
00:24:57,863 --> 00:24:59,863
WAS "I SHOT THE SHERIFF,"       
BUT THEN I REFILTERED IT...     


335
00:24:59,932 --> 00:25:03,601
AND REALIZED IT WAS             
"BUNGLE IN THE JUNGLE."         
                    MM-HMM.     


336
00:25:05,238 --> 00:25:07,170
        HOW MUCH LONGER, BROOTS?


337
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:11,842
WELL, BETWEEN BMI's AND ASCAP's 
COMPUTER BASE OF PLAYLISTS,     


338
00:25:12,911 --> 00:25:15,145
IT COULD BE SOME TIME.          


339
00:25:15,214 --> 00:25:19,049
BUT THEN AS SOON                
AS WE GET A HIT,                
AND WE FIND THE STATION,        


340
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:22,386
I'VE PROGRAMMED THE COMPUTER    
TO CALL HERE.                   


341
00:25:22,455 --> 00:25:24,455
THEN-- [ Clears Throat ]        
WE'RE IN BUSINESS.              


342
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:27,458
            WE'RE IN BUSINESS.  
YEAH.                           


343
00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:30,293
                HOW MUCH LONGER?


344
00:25:31,864 --> 00:25:35,932
            WAKE UP.            
            I THINK I'VE GOT IT.


345
00:25:39,704 --> 00:25:42,105
        <i> WE'VE BEEN CLIMBING</i>    
        <i> FOR NINE HOURS.</i>        


346
00:25:42,174 --> 00:25:47,043
        YOU WANT TO TELL ME     
        WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR? 
    THAT.                       


347
00:25:51,984 --> 00:25:54,084
THIS WAS VICTOR'S CAMP.         


348
00:25:55,721 --> 00:26:00,690
THE FORCE<i> IS</i> WITH YOU.          
HOW DID YOU KNOW?               


349
00:26:00,759 --> 00:26:03,560
    SOMETHING ALWAYS BOTHERED ME
    ABOUT SIMPKINS'S BASE CAMP. 


350
00:26:03,629 --> 00:26:05,562
<i>THE CAMP WAS WAY TOO LOW</i>        
<i>ON THE MOUNTAIN TO OBSERVE...</i>   


351
00:26:05,631 --> 00:26:10,834
<i>THE NESTING PATTERNS OF EAGLES,</i> 
<i>BECAUSE THEY ALWAYS NEST</i>        
<i>AT THE HIGHEST POINT.</i>           


352
00:26:23,148 --> 00:26:27,117
    -<i> WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?</i>    
    - THE PLANE THAT SCARED     
      LITTLE BOB.               


353
00:26:35,561 --> 00:26:39,129
THE PILOT'S DEAD.               
THERE WAS A BULLET              
IN HIS HEAD.                    


354
00:26:39,198 --> 00:26:42,833
- OH, MY GOD.                   
- I FOUND TRACES OF NARCOTICS   
  IN THE BACK.                  


355
00:26:45,304 --> 00:26:49,940
    - AND I FOUND THIS.         
    - DELIVER YOUR DRUGS,       
      PICK UP YOUR MONEY.       


356
00:26:50,009 --> 00:26:53,910
YOU DON'T FILE A FLIGHT PLAN    
WITH A RUN LIKE THIS,           
SO IF YOUR PLANE CRASHES--      


357
00:26:53,979 --> 00:26:58,382
    - NO ONE LOOKS FOR YOU.     
    - SOMEBODY WAS UP HERE.     


358
00:27:08,728 --> 00:27:13,564
THERE'S TWO SETS OF FOOTPRINTS, 
BUT THEY BOTH COME              
FROM DIFFERENT DIRECTIONS.      


359
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:19,803
THEN ONE CHASES THE OTHER...    
THAT WAY.                       


360
00:27:21,073 --> 00:27:24,674
        <i> HE HEARD THE CRASH,</i>    
        <i> CAME DOWN HERE.</i>        


361
00:27:25,944 --> 00:27:27,944
    HE JUST WANTED TO HELP.     


362
00:27:29,348 --> 00:27:31,415
<i>HE SAW THE MURDER.</i>              


363
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:37,754
    HE'S RUNNING.               
     HE'S RUNNING FOR HIS LIFE. 


364
00:27:37,823 --> 00:27:40,023
            <i> VICTOR SIMPKINS.</i>   


365
00:27:40,091 --> 00:27:43,293
        AND WHO WAS CHASING HIM?


366
00:27:43,362 --> 00:27:47,530
WHO WAS BLOWING UP STUMPS       
WHEN BOB HEARD THE PLANE?       


367
00:27:47,599 --> 00:27:52,235
- CONRAD.                       
- CONRAD IS LEADING THE SEARCH. 


368
00:27:55,641 --> 00:28:00,510
-WHAT WERE YOU-- HOW DID YOU--  
-TRUST IN THE FORCE, YOUNG JEDI.


369
00:28:01,780 --> 00:28:04,314
I SAW YOUR LASER DISK           
LAST NIGHT.                     


370
00:28:07,286 --> 00:28:09,986
        THOSE PRINTS HEAD DOWN  
        TO BOX CANYON.          


371
00:28:11,424 --> 00:28:13,356
WE'LL START THAT WAY TOMORROW.  


372
00:28:20,065 --> 00:28:22,900
I HOPE VICTOR SIMPKINS IS UNDER 
SOME KIND OF COVER TONIGHT.     


373
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:28,872
BECAUSE IF HE'S NOT,            
HE'S NOT GOING TO MAKE IT.      


374
00:28:30,275 --> 00:28:33,443
NEITHER ARE WE,                 
UNLESS WE FIND SOME SHELTER.    


375
00:28:34,847 --> 00:28:36,880
                <i> I KNOW A PLACE.</i>


376
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:46,823
        WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME? 
WHAT?                           


377
00:28:46,892 --> 00:28:48,825
            SHUT UP!            
                LET HIM ALONE.  


378
00:28:48,894 --> 00:28:51,861
            [ Moe ]             
            YOU TOO. COME HERE. 
    [ Larry, Shemp Groaning ]   


379
00:28:51,930 --> 00:28:53,730
        [ Larry, Shemp ]        
        MMMM.                   
        THERE.                  


380
00:28:53,799 --> 00:28:57,834
    - [ Larry, Shemp Groaning ] 
    - MORONS.                   


381
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:09,646
[ Jarod ]                       
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU...        
ABOUT WOMEN.                    


382
00:29:09,715 --> 00:29:11,715
[ Rewinding ]                   


383
00:29:11,783 --> 00:29:15,586
ABOUT WOMEN.                    
[ Rewinding ]                   


384
00:29:15,654 --> 00:29:17,654
ABOUT WOMEN.                    


385
00:29:41,180 --> 00:29:44,948
        <i> YOU KNOW, GIRLS MATURE</i> 
        <i> FASTER THAN BOYS.</i>      


386
00:29:54,159 --> 00:29:57,760
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


387
00:30:11,376 --> 00:30:14,077
<i>[ Thunderclap ]</i>                 


388
00:30:15,581 --> 00:30:18,348
            NOTHING LIKE        
            A HOME-COOKED MEAL. 


389
00:30:18,417 --> 00:30:20,417
SO I'M TOLD.                    


390
00:30:29,528 --> 00:30:31,527
WHEN I WAS A CHILD,             


391
00:30:34,633 --> 00:30:37,401
I WAS TAKEN--                   


392
00:30:37,469 --> 00:30:39,469
<i>AT LEAST I THINK I WAS TAKEN--</i>  


393
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:48,911
<i>THEY MADE ME DO THINGS--</i>        


394
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:52,181
THINGS THAT HURT OTHER--        


395
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:56,486
        YOU DON'T HAVE TO       
        TELL ME ANYTHING.       
<i>I KNOW.</i>                         


396
00:30:56,555 --> 00:31:02,358
I NEVER TOLD ANYBODY BEFORE,    
BUT I WANT TO TELL YOU.         


397
00:31:07,365 --> 00:31:09,365
I DON'T KNOW WHO I AM.          


398
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:18,808
        YOU'RE JAROD,           
        AND YOU'RE HERE WITH ME.


399
00:31:24,615 --> 00:31:26,616
[ Chuckles ]                    


400
00:31:30,255 --> 00:31:35,525
HOW OLD WERE YOU                
WHEN YOU LEFT ARGENTINA?        
                    THIRTEEN.   


401
00:31:35,594 --> 00:31:38,227
WAS IT BECAUSE OF               
THE<i> GUERRA SUCIA?</i>               


402
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:42,064
I SAW THE SCARS ON YOUR BACK.   


403
00:31:48,039 --> 00:31:50,206
                    I WAS EIGHT.


404
00:31:50,275 --> 00:31:52,742
        THEY CAME AND TOOK US   
        FOR NO REASON AT ALL.   


405
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:58,047
        MY FATHER               
        PUBLISHED A NEWSPAPER.  


406
00:31:58,116 --> 00:32:00,683
        MY MOTHER MET HIM       
        WHEN SHE WAS A REPORTER.


407
00:32:03,221 --> 00:32:05,387
        BUT SHE HADN'T WORKED   
        FOR YEARS.              


408
00:32:05,456 --> 00:32:08,458
    SHE WAS TOO BUSY RAISING ME.


409
00:32:10,862 --> 00:32:12,796
    THEY WOKE US UP             
    IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT. 


410
00:32:12,864 --> 00:32:16,031
        <i> I COULD HEAR</i>           
        <i> MY MOTHER SCREAMING,</i>   
        <i> CURSING AT THEM.</i>       


411
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:20,703
        I NEVER HEARD HER       
        SWEAR LIKE THAT BEFORE. 


412
00:32:24,575 --> 00:32:29,511
<i>THEY TOOK US TO THIS PLACE--</i>    
<i>THIS HORRIBLE PLACE.</i>            


413
00:32:33,084 --> 00:32:35,084
    I NEVER SAW THEM AGAIN.     


414
00:32:38,222 --> 00:32:40,223
        THEY BEAT ME.           


415
00:32:43,261 --> 00:32:47,997
            THEY-- THEY--       


416
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:52,268
        [ Whispering ]          
        I'M SORRY.              


417
00:32:52,337 --> 00:32:56,039
    THEY WANTED ME TO LIE       
    ABOUT MY PARENTS--          


418
00:32:57,842 --> 00:33:02,645
THAT THEY HATED THE GENERALS,   
HAD PLOTTED AGAINST THEM.       


419
00:33:03,715 --> 00:33:06,081
                <i> I WOULDN'T LIE.</i>


420
00:33:08,185 --> 00:33:10,353
    FINALLY, THEY LET ME GO.    


421
00:33:11,556 --> 00:33:15,992
THEY PUT ME WITH SOME FAMILY,   


422
00:33:17,429 --> 00:33:21,730
BUT NO ONE WILL TALK TO ME      
ABOUT MY PARENTS.               


423
00:33:26,404 --> 00:33:28,805
    THEY HAD DISAPPEARED.       


424
00:33:39,951 --> 00:33:45,755
        <i> THEN THE GENERALS LEFT,</i>
        <i> AND I CAME HERE.</i>       


425
00:33:48,459 --> 00:33:51,861
    I DON'T KNOW IF MY PARENTS  
    ARE DEAD OR ALIVE.          


426
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:59,068
    I DON'T KNOW EITHER.        


427
00:34:00,438 --> 00:34:02,906
    I MISS THEM VERY MUCH.      


428
00:34:05,977 --> 00:34:09,345
[ Sobbing ]                     
                I KNOW, I KNOW. 


429
00:34:09,413 --> 00:34:11,280
        I KNOW, I KNOW, I KNOW. 


430
00:34:11,349 --> 00:34:13,716
                SHH. SHH. SHH.  


431
00:34:17,622 --> 00:34:20,189
    SHH. SHH.                   


432
00:34:34,338 --> 00:34:37,273
I KNOW THIS IS GOING            
TO SOUND CRAZY.                 


433
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:42,177
I'VE NEVER--                    
                            SHH.


434
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:21,783
I JUST WANT TO KNOW WHO I AM.   


435
00:35:23,787 --> 00:35:25,787
I CAN STAND ANYTHING FOR THAT.  


436
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:53,750
                <i> [ Tapping ]</i>    


437
00:35:58,389 --> 00:36:01,390
        <i> [ Tapping Continues ]</i>  


438
00:36:02,860 --> 00:36:04,827
        [ Snorting ]            


439
00:36:09,667 --> 00:36:11,668
<i>[ Pats ]</i>                        


440
00:36:13,404 --> 00:36:15,771
        <i> [ Snorting Continues ]</i> 


441
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:18,073
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>IS THAT PIG</i>                     
<i>WEARING A BASEBALL CAP?</i>         


442
00:36:20,411 --> 00:36:23,446
            THERE YOU ARE.      
            LOOK AT HIM.        


443
00:36:23,515 --> 00:36:25,481
        ALL THE STRESS          
        MADE HIM LOSE WEIGHT.   


444
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:27,850
    <i> SOOEY, SOOEY, SOOEY, SOOEY!</i>


445
00:36:27,919 --> 00:36:30,052
            <i> COME HERE YOU, BOY.</i>


446
00:36:30,121 --> 00:36:33,456
-<i> [ Jarod ] IS THAT YOUR PIG?</i>   
- PIG? HE'S NO PIG.             


447
00:36:33,525 --> 00:36:36,292
HE'S MY PARTNER IN              
A BURGEONING MUSHROOM EMPIRE.   


448
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:39,294
LITTLE BOB.                     
                    LITTLE BOB. 


449
00:36:39,363 --> 00:36:42,465
    - THE ONE AND ONLY.         
    - AND YOUR CROP             
      WOULD BE TRUFFLES?        


450
00:36:42,533 --> 00:36:45,167
        THE FINEST DAMN NOSE    
        IN THESE UNITED STATES. 


451
00:36:45,236 --> 00:36:47,269
        FOUND A MOTHER LODE TOO.


452
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:49,304
        WE COULD'VE BEEN RICH,  
        TILL SOMEONE WENT       
        AND BLOWED UP...        


453
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:52,274
THE OLD MINE SHAFT WHERE HE     
DISCOVERED OVER A TON OF THEM.  


454
00:36:52,343 --> 00:36:55,578
    - MINE SHAFT?               
    - YEAH, THE ONE DOWN        
      IN BOX CANYON.            


455
00:36:55,647 --> 00:36:57,913
        BLOWED IT THE SAME DAY  
        THAT PLANE FLEW OVER.   


456
00:36:57,982 --> 00:37:00,182
            <i> COME HERE, BIG BOY.</i>
             <i> COME ON.</i>          


457
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:15,765
FOOTPRINTS. TWO SETS.           


458
00:37:15,833 --> 00:37:19,535
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>TWO GO IN,</i>                      
<i>BUT ONLY ONE COMES OUT.</i>         


459
00:37:22,140 --> 00:37:26,342
CONRAD CHASED VICTOR,           
TRYING TO SILENCE HIM.          


460
00:37:27,778 --> 00:37:30,946
VICTOR RAN IN HERE TO HIDE.     


461
00:37:31,015 --> 00:37:36,986
CONRAD, RUNNING SHORT OF TIME,  
DECIDED TO BLOW OUT             
THE ENTRANCE, SEALING HIM IN.   


462
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:42,291
THE FORCE IS WITH ME.           
[ Chuckles ]                    


463
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:49,598
                VICTOR! VICTOR! 


464
00:37:49,667 --> 00:37:52,535
<i>[ Nia ]</i>                         
<i>VICTOR!</i>                         
                VICTOR!         


465
00:37:52,603 --> 00:37:56,439
            - VICTOR!           
            - VICTOR!           


466
00:38:17,862 --> 00:38:21,464
        - [ Gasping ]           
        - VICTOR.               


467
00:38:21,533 --> 00:38:23,666
<i>[ Nia ]</i>                         
<i>VICTOR.</i>                         
                VICTOR.         


468
00:38:25,136 --> 00:38:27,069
            [ Coughing ]        


469
00:38:27,137 --> 00:38:30,739
        IT'S OKAY.              
        YOU'RE GOING TO BE OKAY.


470
00:38:33,077 --> 00:38:35,978
        [ Keyboarding ]         


471
00:38:39,183 --> 00:38:41,517
        [ Beeping ]             


472
00:38:41,585 --> 00:38:45,087
    [ Imitating Three Stooges,  
      Gibberish ]               


473
00:38:45,156 --> 00:38:46,689
        [ Clang ]               
        [ Horn Honks ]          


474
00:38:46,757 --> 00:38:51,294
    ♪♪ [ Instrumental ]         


475
00:38:51,362 --> 00:38:53,295
    ♪♪ [ Theme From             
        <i> The Three Stooges</i> ]    


476
00:38:59,203 --> 00:39:02,305
        [ Shuts Off ]           


477
00:39:02,373 --> 00:39:04,540
    -<i> [ Sydney ] MISS PARKER?</i>   
    -<i> WHAT?</i>                     


478
00:39:04,609 --> 00:39:09,277
    WE'VE TRACED THE SONG       
    TO A SMALL RADIO STATION    
    IN NORTH-CENTRAL OREGON.    


479
00:39:09,346 --> 00:39:13,882
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               
<i>[ Radio Chatter ]</i>               


480
00:39:13,952 --> 00:39:16,685
        TOLUCA NATIONAL FOREST, 
        RANGER CONRAD SPEAKING. 


481
00:39:16,754 --> 00:39:19,188
<i>[ Big Bob ]</i>                     
<i>UH, YEAH, THIS IS BOB CARSEY.</i>   


482
00:39:19,257 --> 00:39:22,024
<i>RANGER CONRAD, I THINK I FOUND</i>  
<i>THE SIMPKINS KID.</i>               


483
00:39:22,093 --> 00:39:24,826
    <i> WHERE IS HE? IS HE ALIVE?</i>  


484
00:39:24,895 --> 00:39:27,429
    I COULDN'T TELL.            
    HE WAS TRAPPED              
    BEHIND A ROCKFALL...        


485
00:39:27,498 --> 00:39:30,699
INSIDE THE OLD COPPER MINE      
IN BOX CANYON.                  


486
00:39:30,768 --> 00:39:34,236
I COULD BARELY MAKE             
A HOLE BIG ENOUGH               
TO LOOK IN AND SEE.             


487
00:39:34,305 --> 00:39:36,806
            I'M ON MY WAY.      


488
00:39:36,874 --> 00:39:39,842
    KOBEY, I NEED YOU HERE      
    TO COORDINATE THE MEN       
    AND THE EQUIPMENT COMING UP.


489
00:39:39,911 --> 00:39:41,844
DO YOU WANT ME                  
TO CALL HIS MOTHER?             
                            NO. 


490
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:44,513
            NOT TILL WE'RE SURE 
            WE HAVE GOOD NEWS.  


491
00:40:00,831 --> 00:40:02,898
<i>[ Clanking ]</i>                    


492
00:40:05,169 --> 00:40:07,169
<i>HEY, SIMPKINS.</i>                  


493
00:40:24,021 --> 00:40:27,356
SIMPKINS. HEY, SIMPKINS.        


494
00:40:29,159 --> 00:40:33,862
        <i> WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME.</i> 
        <i> MY LEGS WERE STARTING</i>  
        <i> TO CRAMP UP.</i>           


495
00:40:33,931 --> 00:40:37,933
        <i> KIND OF LIKE LAZARUS,</i>  
        <i> HUH, CONRAD?</i>           


496
00:40:38,002 --> 00:40:40,936
SO, UH, IS SIMPKINS OKAY?       


497
00:40:41,005 --> 00:40:45,140
YOU MEAN IS HE ALIVE,           
SO HE CAN TESTIFY AGAINST YOU?  


498
00:40:45,209 --> 00:40:48,477
    - YOU BETCHA.               
    - SO, WHY DIDN'T YOU        
      JUST CALL THE POLICE?     


499
00:40:57,388 --> 00:40:59,354
<i>YOU'RE AFTER</i>                    
<i>WHAT'S IN THE PLANE.</i>            


500
00:40:59,423 --> 00:41:02,758
    - HEY, THERE'S A LOT MORE   
      WHERE THAT CAME FROM.     
    - NO DEAL.                  


501
00:41:02,827 --> 00:41:04,793
<i>[ Booming ]</i>                     


502
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:09,798
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>KIND OF SPOOKY IN HERE,</i>         
<i>ISN'T IT?</i>                       


503
00:41:12,069 --> 00:41:15,037
<i>DO YOU THINK THIS IS WHAT</i>       
<i>HELL IS LIKE, STAN?</i>             


504
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:20,575
IMAGINE WHAT IT'S LIKE          
TO BE TRAPPED IN HERE,          


505
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:23,712
<i>AND NO ONE</i>                      
<i>CAN HEAR YOU SCREAMING.</i>         


506
00:41:23,781 --> 00:41:25,780
    THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY OUT!   


507
00:41:28,686 --> 00:41:31,820
<i>HEY, CONRAD,</i>                    
<i>I'D STAND BACK IF I WERE YOU.</i>   


508
00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:37,793
                NO!             


509
00:41:57,282 --> 00:41:59,848
                JAROD!          


510
00:41:59,917 --> 00:42:02,618
        DON'T LEAVE ME HERE,    
        JAROD! PLEASE!          


511
00:42:02,686 --> 00:42:04,687
    OH, DON'T WORRY.            


512
00:42:04,755 --> 00:42:08,857
I'LL LEAD THE SEARCH FOR        
YOU PERSONALLY... IN A FEW DAYS.


513
00:42:08,926 --> 00:42:13,028
                JAROD! JAROD!   


514
00:42:52,903 --> 00:42:56,038
I KNOW HOW TO DO MANY THINGS,   


515
00:42:59,576 --> 00:43:01,710
BUT I DON'T KNOW HOW TO DO THIS.


516
00:43:04,181 --> 00:43:06,448
I KNOW YOU HAVE TO GO.          


517
00:43:10,954 --> 00:43:13,255
    PEOPLE ARE LOOKING FOR ME.  


518
00:43:14,826 --> 00:43:16,926
<i>IF I STAY,</i>                      
<i>YOU'D BE IN DANGER.</i>             


519
00:43:18,963 --> 00:43:20,896
        YOU MAY ALREADY BE.     


520
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:25,768
    I KNOW HOW TO               
    TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.        


521
00:43:25,837 --> 00:43:28,170
        I HOPE YOU FIND         
        WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.


522
00:43:38,849 --> 00:43:41,783
YOU'VE ALREADY HELPED ME        
FIND A PART OF IT.              


523
00:43:55,099 --> 00:43:59,167
    <i> ADIÓS, MI VIDA.</i>            


524
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,684
♪♪ [ Theme From                 
<i>     The Three Stooges ]</i>        


525
00:44:57,828 --> 00:45:00,029
<i>[ Car Doors Opening, Closing ]</i>  


526
00:45:02,666 --> 00:45:06,702
    HAVE YOU SEEN THIS MAN?     
                YES.            


527
00:45:06,771 --> 00:45:10,739
HE WAS TALL, HANDSOME,          
A LITTLE MOLE ON HIS RIGHT EYE. 


528
00:45:10,808 --> 00:45:14,643
- YES?                          
- HE STAYED FOR A FEW NIGHTS.   


529
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:17,746
- HE'S GONE NOW.                
- DID HE SAY WHERE HE WAS GOING?


530
00:45:17,815 --> 00:45:23,719
<i>NO, BUT HE DID MENTION SOMETHING</i>
<i>ABOUT LOVING ARGENTINA.</i>         


531
00:45:29,894 --> 00:45:31,860
DO YOU THINK HE'LL COME BACK?   


532
00:45:31,929 --> 00:45:34,163
                I HOPE SO.      


533
00:45:43,907 --> 00:45:45,907
        <i> [ Car Engine Starts ]</i>  


534
00:46:37,861 --> 00:46:38,894
            [ Mews ]            


